
Function: CURTIME

Syntax:   (CURTIME)
    or:   (CURRENT-TIME)

Returns:

 A list of 3 integers, representing the current time in hours,
 minutes, and seconds.

Processing:

 The current time of day is determined, and a list is made of the
 2 components.

Errors signaled:

 None.

Notes:

 If a garbage collection occurs while building the list, the time
 returned may be inaccurate; but it will reflect the time before
 the GC occurred.

Examples:

; (CURTIME)     ==> (8 10 31)   ; at 8:10 AM and 31 seconds
; (CURTIME)     ==> (13 14 15)  ; at 1:14 PM and 15 seconds

